headline: 3 Healthcare Stocks Facing Headwinds
summary: From novel pharmaceuticals to telemedicine, most healthcare companies are on a mission to drive better patient outcomes. But speed bumps such as inventory destockings have persisted in the wake of COVID-19, and over the past six months, the industry has pulled back by 12.7%. This drop was worse than the S&P 500’s 7.5% loss.
